.TH GIT-STAGE-BATCH-STOP 1 "May 2026" "git-stage-batch @VERSION@" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
git-stage-batch-stop \- stop the current session
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B git-stage-batch stop
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B stop
removes session state and leaves the index and working tree as they are.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR git-stage-batch (1),
.BR git-stage-batch-abort (1)
